				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Zuk, I think the level 47ish _female_ erudite (Cyanelle) is supposed to drop the book, not the 50ish male (Eldreth).  Though someone said they killed Cyanelle and no book dropped from her either.  Still doesn't mean she couldn't drop it because it was an uncommon drop for her back when she was level 25 or whatever.<BR>
<BR>
Has anyone managed to find a shadowed book to see if Vurgo's text on how to do the quest has changed?  I camped shadowed men for a few hours hoping for another book but none dropped.  I tried many variations on the idea posted elsewhere about getting them to drop a book by handing them 1hs weapons.  I don't think that trick works anymore if it ever did, or it only works with a more specific type of 1hs weapon or something.  I had ended up using an axe and a sword and a scimitar and sword for lack of being able to find two identical swords in the area.  Every time I would give one sword the book the necro normally holds visible would disappear, if that means anything.
