	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hey, Permafrost is a big pain!  *grumble*  But here's how it works...<BR>
<BR>
I'm level 40 and I found that even though I'm Iksar and well hated I could dance around on top of the ice goblins at the entrance to permafrost without them aggroing because they're so green.  Nevertheless I went in invisible.  I conned each goblin and found them all indifferent save for one Goblin Evoker standing next to a solid metal door I had to pass through.  I conned other evokers as indifferent so I don't know why just this one could see invisible.  I held my breath and ran past him and he didn't aggro.  After that nothing saw past invisible.<BR>
<BR>
The Icy goblin spawns in a small round room (a jail cell with 3 hooks in the celing).  It is the middle cell of the 3 southern cells.  Check the map at eqatlas.com and you'll see, it also has a note at the bottom saying where he spawns.<BR>
<BR>
The room will have 4 mobs in it, the southern most of which will either be the icy goblin or a placeholder (always a goblin wizard so far).  The 3 other mobs can be anything, an ice goblin, goblin evoker, goblin wizard, or goblin priest have been seen so far.  Wizards seem to do the most spell damage, evokers second most.  I came when there were 3 priests and one icy goblin.<BR>
<BR>
You're safe next to the door of the cell in the hallway.  I summoned a blue con pet and had him guard next to me so he wouldn't wander around and aggro anything.  I cast stealskin.  I forgot to cast augment death on pet and didn't bother with weapons.  I walked into the room, sending him to attack the Icy Goblin.  I did my best to cast VoS on a couple and then start mezzing.  Every time they got me down a bub of health I would drain spirit on one of them, and sometimes throw in a shock of poison.  Although the priests did a lot of healing they didn't do a lot of damage either (hit for 43 max, usually missed).  We took them all down with about half a bub of my mana left, my pet at half health, and me at full health.  Once broken the camp is a snap, but very boring.<BR>
<BR>
The Icy goblin or placeholder spawns every 24 minutes and seems to always be followed about a minute later by a single spawn to the left of the room.  It would appear that the 3 support mobs don't spawn unless the icy goblin or PH is alive, so if you kill him quick the single left side spawn is the only other one you have to deal with.  Actually scratch that...  I just killed icy and then 5 mins later the middle of the room spawn popped.  So I don't understand how they have it set up but I've never had more then 2 goblins pop at once once the camp is broken.<BR>
<BR>
I had to go to bed after 4 spawns (2 icy goblins carrying nothing and 2 goblin wizards).  The next day I used some better tactics to break the camp.  Cast spirit armor and resist cold on pet, resist cold on myself (some of their spells are cold based but they also use lightning and fire).  Cast augment death.  Gave pet two rusty weapons.  Goblin wizard was up instead of icy, and there was an ice goblin and two evokers in the room.  I stood outside the cell and cast VoS on the wizard.  He came running out and I rooted him.  20 seconds later the ice goblin joined the fight, presumably because he was closest to the door.  My pet seemed to be almost twice as effective and killed the wizard quickly, ice goblin went down soon after.  1.5 bubs of mana spent and steelskin gone I sat down to med (pet at 85% health or so).  Back at full health I went in and killed the two remaining evokers easily.  Still haven't seen the book of frost but at least the next icy goblin dropped permafrost crystals and a fine steal spear.<BR>
<BR>
I think level 39 is probably the minmum level to relatively safely break this camp.  It may also be possible at 34 with some luck.  I'm thinking either barge in and start casting the point blank aoe spell to damage them all (probably won't work on healing priests though), or just send in pet, vos and nuke one of them till it's dead (or almost), then feign death outside the cell.  Med to full and repeat until the camp is broken.  Or just get a higher level person to break it and then you can solo it easily.<BR>
<BR>
So, I hope that's more then enough information for anyone who wants to take this camp.  Good luck.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
